<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-10-18T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-10-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="1085" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1085">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-10-18T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3043. Your mail despatch 1517, July 8. You may reply to Sublime Porte in
                            accordance with your suggestion, calling attention to the seriousness of
                            the violation by the Turkish Government of the American consular
                            seals.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>